---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ArrowIcon from "../assets/svg/arrow.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Penqwin"
  description="Review the privacy policy for Penqwin, the engineering documentation sync platform. Learn how we handle your data and code."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="relative min-h-screen bg-bg-main pt-32 pb-24 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Background Effects (Matching Hero) -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none overflow-hidden">
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid opacity-[0.02] [mask-image:radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,black,transparent_80%)]"
      >
      </div>
      <div
        class="absolute top-[-10%] left-[-10%] w-[600px] h-[600px] bg-primary/5 blur-[120px] rounded-full animate-pulse-slow"
      >
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-text-secondary hover:text-primary transition-colors duration-300 group"
        >
          <ArrowIcon
            class="w-4 h-4 rotate-180 transform group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform"
          />
          <span class="text-sm font-medium">Back to Home</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <h1
          class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-6xl text-text-primary tracking-tight mb-4"
        >
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-text-secondary font-medium">
          Effective Date: <span class="text-text-primary">March 2026</span>
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-12">
        <section>
          <p
            class="text-lg text-text-secondary leading-relaxed first-letter:text-4xl first-letter:font-serif first-letter:text-primary first-letter:mr-2 first-letter:float-left"
          >
            Penqwin is built on the belief that developer trust starts with
            transparency. This policy outlines what data we collect, how we use
            it, and the measures we take to keep it secure when you use our
            documentation platform.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >01.</span
            >
            Data We Collect
          </h2>
          <div class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
              We minimize data collection to only what is functionally
              necessary:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Account Information:</strong> When
                you sign in via GitHub, we receive your GitHub ID, username, and primary
                email address.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Repository Metadata:</strong> When
                you provide a URL, we access the repository’s public metadata (name,
                description, and file structure) and relevant code diffs to generate
                documentation.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Usage Data:</strong> We collect
                basic telemetry (browser type, timestamp, and feature usage) to improve
                the platform’s performance.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >02.</span
            >
            How We Process Your Code (The AI Engine)
          </h2>
          <div class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>Penqwin acts as an ephemeral processor.</p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">AI Synthesis:</strong> To generate
                documentation, we send specific code fragments and diffs to our AI
                model providers.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Preview Phase Notice:</strong> During
                this Public Preview, we utilize experimental and preview-grade AI
                models to provide the latest documentation features. Please be aware
                that, depending on the specific preview model in use, data processed
                during this phase may be utilized by the model providers for research
                and training purposes to improve future AI capabilities.
              </li>
              <!-- <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">No Training:</strong> We do not
                use your proprietary code to train our AI models or any third-party
                models. Your code is processed to generate a response and then discarded
                from the model’s active session.
              </li> -->
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Ephemeral Analysis:</strong> We
                do not store a permanent copy of your source code on our servers.
                We only store the generated documentation that you save within the
                Penqwin editor.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >03.</span
            >
            Your Rights (GDPR & Global Standards)
          </h2>
          <div class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
              Regardless of where you live, we provide the same high standard of
              data rights:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Access & Export:</strong> You can
                request a copy of all data we hold about you.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Deletion:</strong> You can delete
                your account at any time. This will instantly remove your profile
                and all documentation stored in our database.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Revoke Access:</strong> You can
                revoke Penqwin’s access to your GitHub account at any time through
                your GitHub settings.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >04.</span
            >
            Third-Party Services
          </h2>
          <div class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-4">
            <p>
              We use a small number of trusted partners to help run Penqwin:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Hosting:</strong> Vercel / AWS (for
                infrastructure).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">AI Models:</strong> Google / OpenAI
                (for documentation synthesis).
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Authentication:</strong> GitHub
                OAuth (for secure login).
              </li>
              <!-- <li>
                <strong class="text-text-primary">Payments:</strong> Stripe (for future
                billing; we never see your credit card details).
              </li> -->
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >05.</span
            >
            Security
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            We implement industry-standard encryption (TLS 1.3) for all data in
            transit. Since Penqwin is built for engineers, we ensure that our
            GitHub App permissions are "Least Privilege," meaning we only ask
            for the minimum access required to read your code diffs.
          </p>
        </section>

        <!-- <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            class="font-serif text-2xl text-text-primary flex items-center gap-3"
          >
            <span class="text-text-muted text-sm font-mono tracking-tighter"
              >06.</span
            >
            Contact Us
          </h2>
          <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
            If you have questions about your data or want to exercise your
            privacy rights, please contact us at <a
              href="mailto:privacy@penqwin.app"
              class="text-primary hover:underline transition-all"
              >privacy@penqwin.app</a
            >.
          </p>
        </section> -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Custom prose-like styles for minimal control */
  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Selection color */
  ::selection {
    background: rgba(139, 92, 246, 0.2);
    color: #fff;
  }
</style>
